      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 22 六五</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六五：賁於丘園，束帛戔戔，吝，終吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fifth SIX, divided, shows its subject adorned by (the occupants of) the heights and gardens. He bears his roll of silk, small and slight. He may appear stingy; but there will be good fortune in the end.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
